{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Setup a single or a set of tracker instances which will be used inside the app to track events."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@objc"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"setup"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"remoteConfiguration"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@M@SnowplowTracker@objc(cs)SPRemoteConfiguration","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"RemoteConfiguration","identifier":"doc:\/\/SnowplowTracker\/documentation\/SnowplowTracker\/RemoteConfiguration"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"defaultConfiguration","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"defaultBundles","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": [","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@M@SnowplowTracker@objc(cs)SPConfigurationBundle","text":"ConfigurationBundle","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/SnowplowTracker\/documentation\/SnowplowTracker\/ConfigurationBundle"},{"text":"]?, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"defaultConfigurationVersion","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"defaultBundleVersion","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" = NSInteger.min, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"onSuccess","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"@escaping","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ([","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"]?, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ConfigurationState","preciseIdentifier":"c:@M@SnowplowTracker@E@SPConfigurationState","identifier":"doc:\/\/SnowplowTracker\/documentation\/SnowplowTracker\/ConfigurationState","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Void","preciseIdentifier":"s:s4Voida","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"remoteConfiguration","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The remote configuration used to indicate where to download the configuration from."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"defaultBundles","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default configuration passed by default in case there isn’t a cached version and it’s able to download a new one."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"defaultBundleVersion","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version of the default configuration that will be used to compare with the fetched remote config to decide whether to replace it."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"onSuccess","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The callback called when a configuration (cached or downloaded) is set."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It passes two arguments: list of the namespaces associated to the created trackers"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and the state of the configuration – whether it was retrieved from cache or fetched over the network."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app can run multiple tracker instances which will be identified by string "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"namespaces"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The trackers configuration is automatically download from the endpoint indicated in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RemoteConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed as argument. For more details see "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RemoteConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The method is asynchronous and you can receive the list of the created trackers in the callbacks once the trackers are created.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The callback can be called multiple times in case a cached configuration is ready and later a fetched configuration is available.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can also pass as argument a default configuration in case there isn’t a cached configuration and it’s not able to download","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a new one. The downloaded configuration updates the cached one only if the configuration version is greater than the cached one.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Otherwise the cached one is kept and the callback is not called.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"IMPORTANT: The EventStore will persist all the events that have been tracked but not yet sent."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Those events are attached to the namespace."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the tracker is removed or the app relaunched with a different namespace, those events can’t"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be sent to the collector and they remain in a zombie state inside the EventStore."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To remove all the zombie events you can call an internal method "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"removeUnsentEventsExceptForNamespaces"},{"type":"text","text":" on "},{"code":"SPSQLEventStore","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which will delete all the EventStores instanced with namespaces not listed in the passed list.","type":"text"}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/snowplowtracker\/snowplow\/setup(remoteconfiguration:defaultconfiguration:defaultconfigurationversion:onsuccess:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/